      "description": "Throughput split by HTTP method. Unknown verbs collapse to _OTHER by the metric's cardinality guard, so a flood of junk methods from a scanner cannot inflate the series count. POST dominates (ingest + commands); a GET spike is usually UI/operator traffic.",
